57.8	Sephardi_Jews	Sephardi Jews	Sephardi Jews is a general term referring to the descendants of the Jews who lived in the Iberian Peninsula before their expulsion in the Spanish Inquisition. It can also refer to those who use a Sephardic style of liturgy or would otherwise define themselves in terms of the Jewish customs and traditions which originated in the Iberian Peninsula.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/60/Sephardi_Jews_-_mosaic.PNG/300px-Sephardi_Jews_-_mosaic.PNG
